#MEM id=upscaling-pipeline source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/pixel/skills/custom/upscaling-pipeline/SKILL.md savings=4%
M||tx|---
M||name|upscaling-pipeline
M||desc|im and vd upscaling for yv production. Covers tool selection, scale factors, qual thresholds, batch ordering (upscale while nx batch generates), and when to reject post-upscale.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|Upsc|right tool, right scale factor, right qual gate, right batch sequencing.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|Scal|tx|\| Base resolution \| Target platform \| Scale factor \| Output \|
M|Scal|tx|\|----------------\|----------------\|-------------\|--------\|
M|Scal|tx|\| 512×512 \| Any \| 4× \| 2048×2048 \|
M|Scal|tx|\| 768×768 \| Instagram Feed \| 2× \| 1536×1536 (crop to 1080×1080) \|
M|Scal|tx|\| 1024×1024 \| Instagram Feed \| 2× \| 2048×2048 (crop to 1080×1080) \|
M|Scal|| 10|5 \| 2× \| 2048×2560 (crop to 1080×1350) \|
M|Scal|tx|\| 512×912 \| Stories / Reels \| 4× \| 2048×3648 (crop to 1080×1920) \|
M|Scal|**Ru|** Always upscale to at least 2× the final delivery resolution before cropping. Never upscale directly to exact delivery dimensions — leave headroom for crop adjustments.
M|Scal|tx|---
M|Tool|tx|\| Tool \| Best for \| Avoid when \|
M|Tool|tx|\|------\|----------\|-----------\|
M|Tool|tx|\| Real-ESRGAN (4× General) \| Photorealistic images, lifestyle, editorial \| Flat ds or illustration \|
M|Tool|tx|\| Real-ESRGAN (4× Anime) \| Illustration, graphic style \| Realistic photography \|
M|Tool|tx|\| Topaz Gigapixel AI \| Maximum qual, final hero images \| Quick batch runs (slow) \|
M|Tool|tx|\| Stable Diffusion img2img (upscale) \| Adding detail at upscale stage \| When pm fidelity must be preserved exactly \|
M|Tool|tx|\| Lanczos (software) \| Emergency / no tool available \| Never for hero images \|
M|Tool|**De|** Real-ESRGAN 4× General for nz lifestyle/editorial. Real-ESRGAN 4× General for hb people-w/-devices.
M|Tool|tx|---
M|Qual|Run |
M|Qual|tx|\| Check \| Pass \| Fail → Action \|
M|Qual|tx|\|-------\|------\|--------------\|
M|Qual|tx|\| Detail integrity \| Fine details (fabric texture, hair, UI elements) are sharper, not smeared \| Re-upscale w/ different tool \|
M|Qual|tx|\| No hallucinated detail \| Upscaler has not invented new elements not in original \| Reject — return to generation \|
M|Qual|tx|\| No over-sharpening \| Edges look natural, no halo artefacts \| Reduce sharpening setting, re-run \|
M|Qual|tx|\| Face qual \| Face detail is improved, not degraded \| Run face-enhance pass separately \|
M|Qual|tx|\| Text clarity \| Any intentional text is more legible, not distorted \| Run text-focused upscale or reject \|
M|Qual|**Ru|** If an im passes QC before upscaling but fails post-upscale, do not deliver the pre-upscale version. Fix the upscaling. The base im passes; only the upscale technique failed.
M|Qual|tx|---
M|Vide|tx|vd upscaling is slower and riskier than im upscaling. Approach w/ more caution.
M|When|tx|\| Condition \| Action \|
M|When|tx|\|-----------\|--------\|
M|When|tx|\| Output is < 1080p and platform requires 1080p \| Upscale required \|
M|When|tx|\| Output is 1080p and platform requires 1080p \| No upscale needed \|
M|When|tx|\| Output has visible compression artifacts \| Re-gn at higher qual setting instead of upscaling \|
M|When|**Ru|** Re-generation beats upscaling for vd qual issues. Only upscale when re-generation is not feasible (budget, time).
M|Vide|tx|\| Tool \| Use case \|
M|Vide|tx|\|------\|---------\|
M|Vide|tx|\| Topaz vd AI \| Primary tool — frame interpolation + upscale \|
M|Vide|tx|\| Real-ESRGAN (vd mode) \| Faster, lower qual than Topaz \|
M|Vide|**De|**
M|Vide|- Mo|Proteus (for realistic cn) / Iris (for faces)
M|Vide|- En|2× scale
M|Vide|- Fr|match original (do not change frame rate at upscale stage)
M|Post|tx|\| Check \| Pass \| Fail \|
M|Post|tx|\|-------\|------\|------\|
M|Post|tx|\| Motion smoothness \| Motion unchanged or improved \| Motion blur or ghosting introduced \|
M|Post|tx|\| Face stability \| Face detail improved \| Face flickering or morphing introduced by upscaler \|
M|Post|tx|\| Edge detail \| Subject edges sharper \| Halo or ringing around edges \|
M|Post|tx|---
M|Batc|Pixe|
M|Batc|tx|```
M|Batc|[Bat|gn] → [Batch A: QC] → [Batch A: Upscale] → [Batch A: Format] → [Deliver]
M|Batc|tx|↓
M|Batc|[Bat|gn] → [Batch B: QC] → [Batch B: Upscale] → ...
M|Batc|tx|```
M|Batc|**Ru|** Start Batch B generation while Batch A is upscaling. Never wait for full delivery of Batch A before starting Batch B. The bottleneck is upscaling (slowest stage) — parallel staging keeps the pipeline moving.
M|Batc|**Ex|** Do not start Batch B if Batch A's QC pass rate is < 60%. Investigate pm before spending more generation budget.
M|Batc|tx|---
M|Upsc|Afte|
M|Upsc|tx|```
M|Upsc|tx|[date] — [vt] — [cg] — [tool used] — [scale factor] — [pass rate post-upscale] — [notes]
M|Upsc|tx|```
M|Upsc|tx|If a tool consistently degrades a specific tp of im (e.g., Real-ESRGAN smearing fabric texture), log it and up the tool selection guide in this skill.